-- XM settles with Warner Music, agrees new deal
-- 
-- Fri Dec 21, 2007 2:26pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/12/21/xm-warner-idUSWNAS524220071221

 

 NEW YORK  Dec 21 (Reuters) - XM Satellite Radio XMSR.O
and Warner Music Group WMG.N, the world's third largest music
company, said on Friday they had settled a lawsuit brought by
the music company over XM's portable satellite radio with
advanced recording features. 

  The companies did not disclose terms of the deal, which is
a multi-year agreement that covers current XM radios and future
devices.  XM settled a similar dispute with the world's largest music
company Universal Music Group on Dec. 17.
  (Reporting by  Yinka Adegoke , editing by Leslie Gevirtz)



